    Scope and Contents
Robert Marsh was the first registrar for SSU and this collection documents the occasion of the first day of registration (September 1970) at the Illinois State Fairgrounds, among other early university milestones. This collection consists of photographs, newspaper clippings, original registration documents, memos and newsletters regarding SSU, and the donor's letter written on the first SSU letterhead (pre-cloverleaf SSU logo).  
  
    Source of Acquisition
Robert Marsh  
  
    Method of Acquisition
Marsh forwarded the material to Jeanne Boyle who send them to UIS Archives.  
  
